<div class="soliloquy-caption-inside">A job is a regular activity 
performed in exchange for payment. A person usually begins a job by 
becoming an employee, volunteering, or starting a business. The duration
 of a job may range from an hour (in the case of odd jobs) to a lifetime
 (in the case of some judges). If a person is trained for a certain type
 of job, they may have a profession. The series of jobs a person holds 
in their life is their career.<p></p>
